</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE:Mage talk - specifically our pets</span><hr size=1> I just mentioned this in the mage talk but does anyone else see that about 2 levels after you get your pet you start summoning GREEN pets? I'm level 37 and i can't remember when i summoned a black pet, much less then a yellow one. Where have all the high level summons gone? I mean as we level it seems that our pets slowly lose the race in staying up in level with us. Why arent more people up in arms about this? I mean our pet pretty much equals our class. I mean it seemed to me when they &quot;fixed&quot; the sword of runes they also stealth nerfed our pets. I mean i came on the next day and felt like i was in the twilight zone. My pet didnt taunt as well and i used more mana then i had been. Is this only me or do other people see the same results? Thanks. <p><b><c>Kanien <br>
Mage of the 37th Season <br>
Master Smith(186) <br>
Master Tailor(115)<br>
Master Baker(100) 
Master Brewer (121)</b> </c> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub68.ezboard.com/ustren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(2/18/01 10:46:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE:Mage talk - specifically our pets</span><hr size=1> I know what you mean. It really hard to get a good pet these days. I remember I summoned a pet in CT at 35 and a 26 necro in the group said it was even to her. Now thats just wrong then a 35 magician summons a 26 pet.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sydia>Sydia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(3/6/01 6:23:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE:Mage talk - specifically our pets</span><hr size=1> I've expressed my concern over this in a few threads on here.  I even proposed a quest for an item to help bring the pets a little closer to us here:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showMessage?topicID=583.topic">pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagi...=583.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
The response I've been getting in that thread is that our pets are fine and this would overpower us.  Let me ask you this...are you happy with your pets performance?  Even though they're green are you happy with it's tanking/damage dealing ability?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucobeeblazesummoner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cobee Blazesummoner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(3/6/01 10:06:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE:Mage talk - specifically our pets</span><hr size=1> Admittedly, yes.  My pets do VERY close to the same damage as the main tank of my group as it stands now.  I've also noticed that double attack happens more frequently when I hand my pet two SoR.  Earth pet regen is AWESOME right now, to top that all off.<br>
<br>
